{"CAPE":[{"def":"A piece or point of land, extending beyind the adjacent coast into the sea or a lake; a promonotory; a headland.","pos":""}],"CAPEL":[{"def":"A composite stone (quartz, schorl, and hornlende) in the walls of tin and copper lodes.","pos":""}],"CAPELIN":[{"def":"A small marine fish (Mallotus villosus) of the family Salmonidæ, very abundant on the coasts of Greenland, Iceland, Newfoundland, and Alaska.","pos":""}],"CAPELINE":[{"def":"A hood-shaped bandage for the head, the shoulder, or the stump of an amputated limb.","pos":""}],"CAPELLA":[{"def":"A brilliant star in the constellation Auriga.","pos":""}],"CAPELLANE":[{"def":"The curate of a chapel; a chaplain.","pos":""}],"CAPELLE":[{"def":"The private orchestra or band of a prince or of a church.","pos":""}],"CAPELLET":[{"def":"A swelling, like a wen, on the point of the elbow (or the heel of the hock) of a horse, caused probably by bruises in lying dowm.","pos":""}],"CAPELLMEISTER":[{"def":"The musical director in royal or ducal chapel; a choirmaster.","pos":""}],"CAPER":[{"def":"To leap or jump about in a sprightly manner; to cut capers; to skip; to spring; to prance; to dance.","pos":""}],"CAPERBERRY":[{"def":"See Capper, a plant, 2.","pos":""},{"def":"A species of grouse (Tetrao uragallus) of large size and fine flavor, found in northern Europe and formerly in Scotland; -- called also cock of the woods.","pos":""}],"CAPERCLAW":[{"def":"To treat with cruel playfulness, as a cat treats a mouse; to abuse.","pos":""}],"CAPERER":[{"def":"One who capers, leaps, and skips about, or dances.","pos":""}]}